I'm a big fan of the Critical Mass Video series, I have just about every one of them so, with that being said, I'm able to give a great comparison and be critical at the same time. Maid Service, as far as content, is about my least favorite out of the entire series and here's why.

Maid Service is an S&M based anime hentai video, and as such, it explores all things S&M throughout the two episodes. All of the girls in the story are unwilling to be sexual partners with the main character, so if you're into that, then that's a plus. However, if you're not into that, get used to the idea of seeing characters forced to do sexual acts against their will for some reason or another.

Typically, what you would see in a two-episode Critical Mass Video is about 4 solid sex scenes lasting for a minute or two, but Maid Service had invariably more scenes that seemed to last longer than the usual stint. I want to say the amount of sex scenes is about 6-10, which is usually a great thing, but it left the story severely lacking in any development that would cause you to care about the characters or their situations. Now, the idea isn't to care about the characters, or even the story really, we all know why we watch these videos. But it makes it easier to enjoy the video when the story has a strong base, a base in which the sex scenes can be built off of.

Once I saw the ending of the story, I didn't even bother re-enjoying previous scenes, it had me so disgusted that I turned it off completely and simply switched to a different Critical Mass Video. Save your money, enjoy another Critical Mass Video or even something else, you'll be better off in the long run having not seen this seriously messed up show. Still, for it's original effort and the sheer amount of sex scenes, I'll give this a 5/5.
